  <steps>
    <step order="1">Verify task 103 = ✅ in TASK-INDEX (integration tests green is gating for deploy).</step>
    <step order="2">Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` on `Sprk.Bff.Api.csproj` — must surface zero new HIGH-severity CVEs vs Phase 3 baseline.</step>
    <step order="3">Build BFF release: `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`. Measure compressed output size + delta vs prior Phase 4 baseline (must remain ≤60 MB per ADR-029).</step>
    <step order="4">Invoke `bff-deploy` skill targeting `bff-dev` App Service. Monitor deployment to completion.</step>
    <step order="5">Smoke-test BFF endpoints: `/ping` returns 200; `GET /api/ai/playbooks/by-code/summarize-document-chat` returns 200; `POST /api/memory/promotions/{nonexistent}/approve` returns 404 ProblemDetails.</step>
    <step order="6">Build SpaarkeAi code page: `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` then `npm run build:prod` per CLAUDE.md.</step>
    <step order="7">Invoke `code-page-deploy` skill for SpaarkeAi to Dataverse dev environment.</step>
    <step order="8">Smoke-test code page in browser: load SpaarkeAi, open ContextPane, verify console shows `usePaneEvent('memory', ...)` subscription registered (no errors).</step>
    <step order="9">Spot-check App Insights for tier-1 hygiene — verify no document content / query text / fact text in logs from recent deployments.</step>
    <step order="10">Write deploy report to `notes/handoffs/104-phase4-deploy.md` — publish-size delta, vuln scan result, smoke-test results.</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 104 → ✅; current-task.md → ready for 105.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Bash">dotnet publish + size measurement + vuln scan; npm install/build for code-page</tool>
    <tool name="Skill">bff-deploy skill; code-page-deploy skill</tool>
    <tool name="Read">Deploy artifact outputs + App Service health</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Deploy report at notes/handoffs/</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="deploy">BFF API deployed to bff-dev App Service</output>
    <output type="deploy">SpaarkeAi code page deployed to Dataverse dev environment</output>
    <output type="docs">notes/handoffs/104-phase4-deploy.md — publish-size delta + vuln scan + smoke-test results</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF `/ping` returns 200 post-deploy.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`/api/ai/playbooks/by-code/summarize-document-chat` returns 200 with valid playbook payload.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`POST /api/memory/promotions/{id}/approve` returns 404 ProblemDetails for nonexistent ID.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SpaarkeAi loads in browser; ContextPane mounts; `memory` channel subscription registers without console error.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta reported; cumulative ≤60 MB per NFR-01 / ADR-029.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Zero new HIGH-severity CVEs vs Phase 3 baseline.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">App Insights spot-check confirms no tier-1 content leakage.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Use `bff-deploy` + `code-page-deploy` skills — do not author bespoke deploy scripts. If the deploy fails midway, do NOT roll back manually; capture logs, escalate per CLAUDE.md §6.
  </notes>

